This paper deals with Sketch-Based Image Retrieval (SBIR), which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques for image retrieval. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a generative approach based on Stacked Adversarial Network (SAN) and Siamese Network (SN), which involves deep learning techniques. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed approach on TU-Berlin and Sketchy databases, which are commonly used in multimedia and image retrieval research. Therefore, cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also likely categories.
